rest_of_day_open: I'm praying it is easier than last week.  An ongoing dental emergency in my household has gummed up the works and, we don't have any emergency savings so we are praying on our insurance to do what it's supposed to.  Also, a water pipe broke under our house and but, luckily our landowner owns a plumbing company so that won't set me back financially.
critical_positive:
Everything worked well. 

The gentleman I spoke with was/is incredibly pleasant and, we chatted about anything and, everything with ease and, I believe mutual curiosity and, enjoyment.  We had a lot in common but, without knowing a ton of specifics about each other we established early on that we were personable and, could have a conversation with just about anybody about whatever and be at ease.
critical_negative: There was nothing that didn't work well.  The gentleman, as I said, was a joy to speak with and, his warm personality shone brightly as we chatted.  Suffice it to say that we could have chatted for an hour or, more easily if that was the 'job' we were given.

rest_of_day_open: This week is very exciting because I am doing two things: one I am starting with a new therapist to work on some personal issues.  Two, I am interviewing for a very good job with a very good company.  I changed careers about 6 months ago, and though I'm glad I took the plunge, it was a change I wish I had not made.  Eager to get back to what I know and love.
critical_positive: it worked well for a couple reasons.  She was very communicative, warm and attractive, so it made me want to engage with her.  Also, she has an interesting background, being born in CA, growing up in PA Dutch Country and then touring the US when she turned 18.  A true free spirit.
critical_negative: My family came home in the middle of the video, so I had to engage with them for a couple moments, which distracted us from our conversation.  As the children settled into home and became noisier, I had to move to a different room to maintain focus.  But we overcame.
